## Example entry (✅ good — keep this style)

### VR-002 — SendGrid (Twilio)
- **Role in this project:** Transactional email delivery — password reset, order confirmation, refund notification, monthly customer statement. NOT marketing campaigns (those go through HubSpot per VR-007).
- **Adopted:** 2023-04-12 (replaces: in-house SMTP via Postfix on a managed VM — see [[anti-decisions]] AD-001 for why)
- **Chosen because:**
  - Delivery rate to .br domains measured at 98.4% over a 30-day spike vs 89% for in-house SMTP (gmail.com inboxing was the main pain).
  - Webhook event stream for bounce/spam-report integrated with our customer-quality service in 2 days; alternative providers required custom polling.
  - Native template editor lets non-engineers (marketing ops) iterate copy without engineering PRs.
- **Alternatives considered:**
  - AWS SES — 30% cheaper but deliverability to .br consumer domains weaker in our test; lacks per-template analytics UI.
  - Mailgun — comparable feature set, but 2022 security incident (subprocessor breach) made legal hesitant.
- **Lock-in surface:** Dynamic Template engine (~14 templates use SendGrid handlebars helpers), Event Webhook subscriber, suppression list managed in SendGrid UI by marketing-ops (not in our DB), inbound parse for `replies@`.
- **Churn cost (estimated):** medium — ~3 person-weeks to migrate templates + rewire event webhook + reproduce suppression-list authority; legal review of new provider DPA adds 1-2 weeks.
- **Cost tier (sanitized):** sub-$1k/mo at current volume; pricing scales linearly with sends.
- **Account owner (internal):** Bia (Customer Success) holds the SendGrid login; renewal annually each March.
- **Vendor contact (if applicable):** standard support tier (no dedicated CSM).
- **Risk watch:** Twilio's broader cost-cutting since 2023 — keep an eye on SendGrid feature deprecations or pricing rebrands. Migration plan should be revisited if Twilio announces SendGrid spin-off or restructure.
- **Related:** ADR-009 (transactional vs marketing email separation), BR-019 (LGPD: any email about a customer's data triggers a log entry in `customer_communication_log`), [[anti-decisions]] AD-001 (in-house Postfix), [[incident-log]] INC-004 (Postfix relay outage that triggered this migration).
- **Captured:** 2025-10-15 by alice

